p imports concise, so I'm crafting the `RecordsHelpersDynamicAccessTest` class with relevant tests. For the assertions, I need to decide on how to check map entries effectively without losing order. Using `assertThat` to check the key set or entries is the direction I’m thinking!\n\n**Examining SampleRecord behavior**\n\nI'm looking at the `SampleRecord` definition, which has an auxiliary constructor allowing me to create a record with `-1` as the ID and `true` as active when only a name is passed. When deserializing from `{\"name\":\"Ada\"}`, it yields the canonical constructor result of `(0, \"Ada\", false)`, which is a nice assertion to have.\n\nI’m contemplating whether to add a third test for serialization and deserialization round-trip, but I think it may not be necessary. I need to ensure there's a metadata entry.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f177e74ce86ea830169f028aed2f0819193ffc24522ebeae3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8CjNNftWAATGMei8UYc8mlnilccnEeB6OMvxkniYxY77xkX8SJl5kIE68QWK24926_Qg7vnxbaAC4m7zZ3kvYf0WcynbPsJIwKLwIKXflpKtJZ31iQb6_DLxt3W4O8hYP0PCFsIlALVKGJpUbWLSPPsApciArIIs5_GKE9MMY2e69GPpM3UeMD6qKGZH4DVWWzkq20UaEl83H4Q5mQ4WjGPF2ZzZI_uvIZz49XJaAkfHKN_M--J9goStlFasYkWgTcuz_Gs3l6LhRlB-mAwqDQ-qY4zVgp1P40jR074z0-xAjtaQ9yx4iHv4l2M0R1lYqqTZu7jVQYmANIxz92NVgQCNWh62I0Z5ZBnRwwPwGx9pXql1AWnBIygCjR_Tx-rxTE_K5X2OXdQyoepzP6BQaDYRAyZygywmXRTn6IXHpMirIItnizkFSec39dJTBz6OCkgK-cJLl4j88FQfno7UF2qT6lYUJ2u6ZCsMRTj0TzL6XjnnF2m7T2DVZXunKvjFz-5VuUcwrnCdQlm4bBjS02bsY4dH0NQ5Wm98ih3-BVbdssjVhar04VCyPbDFOiJAQId5Eg7Q5hbwqXnmAdbU8WoJTRyG_FxJ9S5FzvLZEjLJ4mJyNhMLbtj5qWQj2WBTmyaL25JM7KtuWrl8niqguSekAXT-7YW5tC4NVwbz_sxfFUdsgb7jaPi-xDZjUzl1-jgijUhKdo_uZlNod_6hxi2y5fRrTMIjsUDmKja5Lael7a0MsWKCNXapMBOGZvrjHrbvg4mwxEKoJqfyzyli3sEPEl6liYMvAveTxYZYB8RdTEss4_pRBdFwS0u4296cLRwGBbbEN2gZ3CJHFiXh3cBwn53l-8Z49hCy6_ZB4Hz6HwqIx36sbcIBn1bk6EvNUeHagkwqpdSIqG6gzbWEKH4YxXIqY9QueDcAoRQ5VGwn6UIxKgMLHf5QQxxoRu7MiT2Wgp_TdTC-rBAs0LJsm30s0vd-yuhZFU64jep4TM9cB_1VcCU9kUBSq_QXIj